caller_intent: Bob Grumfield, an insurance inspector, is attempting to complete an exterior photo inspection for a property at 11 Mount Vista Drive but is encountering confusion because the address corresponds to a vacant lot instead of the insured property (Robert Budwaneck's new construction). He seeks clarification and resolution.
resolution_steps: Agent Heather acknowledges the address discrepancy and confirms the address is listed as a vacant lot on Zillow.
Heather attempts to contact another Bob (possibly the policyholder) via phone but is unsuccessful, leaving a voicemail.
Heather suggests alternative solutions: taking photos of the vacant lot or arranging a self-inspection if the policyholder cannot be reached.
Heather confirms the address details with Bob and notes the confusion with another Bob from Ohio.
knowledge_required: Address verification using online tools (e.g., Zillow)
Handling discrepancies between policyholder-provided addresses and actual property data
summary: Bob Grumfield, an insurance inspector, is struggling to complete an inspection at 11 Mount Vista Drive, which he believes is a vacant lot instead of the insured property. Alliance Insurance Services agent Heather verifies the address discrepancy via Zillow, attempts to contact the policyholder (unsuccessfully), and proposes alternatives like self-inspection. The call remains unresolved, pending further contact with the policyholder.
